headline: 2 High-Yield Midstream Stocks to Buy Hand Over Fist and 1 to Avoid
summary: For example, Kinder Morgan (NYSE: KMI) has seen a material price advance and now yields a relatively tiny 4.1%.  You can do over two percentage points better with investments in its midstream energy peers Enterprise Products Partners (NYSE: EPD) or Enbridge (NYSE: ENB).
